Professor Jean-Christophe Demers is a fantstic teacher who is always available to answer any questions you may have. I found this class to be very enjoyable and found Professor Demers to one of the most caring and sincere teachers since my studies here at UOttawa. Receiving an A/A+ is easily obtainable. Excellent.

This is a course that is supposed to be very dry and boring, but he made it quite interesting! Would recommend to anybody! He is French-Canadian but his English is actually better than most people I know.
I've actually had fun during this course. The final presentations were interesting and I felt like the professor cared about what we had to say.

Very creative, very funny, very instructive. He looks like a genuine man, and he is very caring for his students. He was very respectful of my particular needs, and I often went to see him at his office for advice. Great professor. Too bad he isn't full time!

His lectures and vocabulary can be confusing but reading over the slides carfully and you can easily understand. Group project went well (A+). Exam was pretty easy. He has both multiple choice questions and development questions which is good for all types of people. Overall, great class.
Its clear he loves what he does, however, sometimes he teaches like we are all in our PHD and not in first year. Not always clear and laptops are not allowed so you must write fast.

C'est un professeur intéressant qui connaît bien sa matière et qui sait la communiquer efficacement par le biais d'exemples. Toutefois, dans certains cas, ses explications sont longues et difficiles à comprendre. Les examens reflétaient bien le contenu du cours et les question boni ont beaucoup aidé à aller chercher des points supplémentaires.

les cours sont plates, et il part souvent  sur des tangentes. Selon moi il n'est pas nécessaire de se presenté aux cours meme si je l'ai fait personnellement. Il semble beaucoup aimer  sa matiere mes ses monologues en salle de classe sont assez vagues et difficiles a suivre.  le cours a un projet de groupe qui vaut 40%, que je n'ai pas apprécié.

Demers est très intéressent et il rend bien la matière. Il a un language soutenu qui  entraine bien aux études sociologiques.  Les lectures sont complémentaires, il assistes toutes les classes avec un powerpoint.  Le contenu se suit.  Très bonne et belle locution.  Je le recommande définitivement.  Ouvert aux étudiants.
his classes are very boring...
He gives some strange but very interesting and informative lectures. Also, he's gorgeous.

He rambles but knows what he's talking about. Every class he seems to spend more than half the time on what we learned in the previous class and he tends to show up late. Lectures are boring only because he rambles and is unclear. However he is helpful after class hours

Ce professeur sait de quoi il parle!!! Il connaît sa matière, mais avant tout il est passionné par elle!!! Il est disponible aux questions, mais il me joue pas au père, ce qui est très bien, nous sommes à l'université quand même!!! Si nous sommes à notre affaire, c'est facile de passer ce cours!!

Chill prof, but he needs to stop elaborating his words so much. Sometimes he brings up really simple concepts and elaborates them with fancy words so much that it just doesn't make sense. Had to use wikipedia sometimes because he used so many fancy words. Midterms are good, but a lot of trick questions, again to do with vocabulary.

Good prof. Midterm exam is reasonable, and the final for the course is a written paper. Only thing that bothered me was that he did not respond to my emails, I had to email my TA for all my questions, but overall, not too bad.
